<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 7:00PM EDT  by NWS Wakefield</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT NORTHWESTERN PERQUIMANS...
NORTHEASTERN BERTIE...HERTFORD...GATES...AND NORTHWESTERN CHOWAN
COUNTIES AND THE SOUTHWESTERN CITY OF SUFFOLK...
At 700 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Roduco, or near
Gatesville, moving southeast at 30 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail are possible with this
storm.
Locations impacted include...
Ahoskie, Hertford, Winfall, Gatesville, Sunbury, Ryland, Suffolk,
Gates, Winton, Cofield, Powellsville, Colerain, Harrellsville, Como,
Tyner, Roduco, Hobbsville, Whaleyville, Belvidere and Rockyhock.</description>
